        "reviewThreads": {
          "nodes": [
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5SuoWG",
                    "body": "As the file `Sheafification` is already quite long, I would suggest doing all of this in a separate file `ConstantSheaf.lean`.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-11-09T12:49:48Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "joelriou"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5Suohb",
                    "body": "This is `(evaluation Cᵒᵖ D).obj (op (⊤_ C))`, so that I am not sure we need a separate definition.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-11-09T12:50:32Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "joelriou"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5SuqL6",
                    "body": "If we do not have it already, this should be generalized to\r\n```lean\r\nabbrev sheafSections : Cᵒᵖ ⥤ Sheaf J D ⥤ D := (sheafToPresheaf J D).flip\r\n```\r\nso that this would be `sheafSections J D).obj (op (⊤_ C)`.\r\n\r\nNote also that for some applications, it should be convenient to have the adjunction `constantSheafAdj` not only for the chosen terminal object, but for any object that is terminal.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-11-09T12:56:48Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "joelriou"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5SurZZ",
                    "body": "Here, I think it is important to define separately the adjunction given by the constant presheaf functor, and then define the sheaf version as the composition of the two adjunctions.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-11-09T13:01:11Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "joelriou"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5SwIIi",
                    "body": "```suggestion\r\nvariable (D : Type w) [Category.{max v u} D]\r\n\r\n/-- The constant presheaf functor is left adjoint to evaluation at a terminal object. -/\r\nnoncomputable def constantPresheafAdj {T : C} (hT : IsTerminal T) :\r\n```\r\nFor this definition, the universe assumption on `D` could be relaxed.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-11-09T17:32:23Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "joelriou"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5SwLKa",
                    "body": "I just removed the explicit universes, Lean figures them out in the correct generality",
                    "createdAt": "2023-11-09T17:41:40Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "dagurtomas"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
